summary.para: This class is available in Office 2007 and above.
When the object is serialized out as xml, it's qualified name is m:r.

remarks.format:
## Remarks [!INCLUDE[openxmlnoticeiso](~/includes/openxmlnoticeiso.md)]
**r (Run)**
This element specifies a run of mathematical text.
[*Example*:
is represented by the following XML:
```xml <m:oMath> <m:e> <m:r> <m:t>j+k</m:t> </m:r> </m:e> </m:oMath> ```
*end example*]
